1
00:00:14,400 --> 00:00:16,210
Is it beautiful?

2
00:00:17,809 --> 00:00:22,839
The yellow lights
are sparkling with energy.

3
00:00:22,839 --> 00:00:24,159
With energy.

4
00:00:26,960 --> 00:00:29,040
Want to have a contest?

5
00:00:30,375 --> 00:00:33,820
To see who can keep it up longer.

6
00:00:33,820 --> 00:00:34,820
Yeah.

7
00:00:35,583 --> 00:00:38,123
<i>I used to be afraid of happy times.</i>

8
00:00:38,995 --> 00:00:41,940
<i>Because the more I enjoyed them,</i>

9
00:00:41,940 --> 00:00:44,650
<i>the more it hurt when they were gone.</i>

10
00:00:46,450 --> 00:00:47,990
<i>I knew that.</i>

11
00:00:49,010 --> 00:00:50,970
<i>Or at least, I should have.</i>

12
00:00:52,970 --> 00:00:58,333
<i>This is a story about the days
when I had an unseen love with you...</i>

13
00:00:58,333 --> 00:01:03,483
<i>who would run beneath the clear sky.</i>

14
00:01:45,230 --> 00:01:47,761
[Episode 1]

15
00:01:47,761 --> 00:01:51,140
<i>My life motto is to avoid
getting deeply involved with people.</i>

16
00:01:52,220 --> 00:01:55,249
<i>I have no interest
in having a rich campus life.</i>

17
00:01:56,060 --> 00:01:58,905
Kakeru, how was your summer break?

18
00:01:58,905 --> 00:02:01,370
It was just okay.

19
00:02:01,370 --> 00:02:03,360
Nothing special happened?

20
00:02:03,360 --> 00:02:05,110
Not really.

21
00:02:05,110 --> 00:02:07,150
Oh! Well, see you later then.

22
00:02:07,150 --> 00:02:08,170
Hey.

23
00:02:08,170 --> 00:02:13,115
<i>Superficial chats and relationships.
That's all I need.</i>

24
00:03:10,960 --> 00:03:15,850
[Can you make it to
Haruto's third-year memorial service?]

25
00:03:22,415 --> 00:03:25,440
Why do I have to go to your class reunion?

26
00:03:25,440 --> 00:03:27,815
They said I could bring a friend.

27
00:03:27,815 --> 00:03:30,120
We're just roommates.

28
00:03:30,120 --> 00:03:31,515
Don't be like that!

29
00:03:31,515 --> 00:03:34,195
Kakeru, you should enjoy college life too!

30
00:03:38,075 --> 00:03:40,707
- Hey, guys!
- Hey.

31
00:03:40,707 --> 00:03:42,977
That looks good!

32
00:03:47,630 --> 00:03:49,770
Let's start with a beer!

33
00:03:58,030 --> 00:04:00,380
Huh? Kakeru?

34
00:04:03,460 --> 00:04:05,370
I can't believe you're here.

35
00:04:07,122 --> 00:04:10,120
So Yuuko and Kakeru go way back, huh?

36
00:04:10,120 --> 00:04:11,910
A touching reunion!

37
00:04:11,910 --> 00:04:13,320
We see each other on campus.

38
00:04:13,320 --> 00:04:15,395
But this is our first night out, right?

39
00:04:15,395 --> 00:04:17,975
You must be happy too, Kakeru.

40
00:04:18,865 --> 00:04:21,270
I'm even more determined to leave
after the first round.

41
00:04:21,270 --> 00:04:23,672
- Why?
- Come on!

42
00:04:25,285 --> 00:04:27,340
Ah, your glass. Twelve o'clock.

43
00:04:27,340 --> 00:04:29,380
Thanks, Yuuko.

44
00:04:32,435 --> 00:04:34,740
Do you have trouble seeing?

45
00:04:34,740 --> 00:04:36,130
Yes, I do.

46
00:04:36,130 --> 00:04:38,210
I can't see at all.

47
00:04:38,210 --> 00:04:39,610
Hmm.

48
00:04:39,610 --> 00:04:42,350
This is Koharu Fuyutsuki.

49
00:04:42,350 --> 00:04:47,080
A bright-eyed freshman, and my best friend.

50
00:04:47,080 --> 00:04:51,120
I've never been to a drinking party,
so I wanted to try it.

51
00:04:51,120 --> 00:04:52,530
That's awesome.

52
00:04:52,530 --> 00:04:54,390
I'm Ushio Narumi.

53
00:04:54,390 --> 00:04:57,840
And sitting across from you is...

54
00:04:57,840 --> 00:04:59,625
Kakeru.

55
00:04:59,625 --> 00:05:01,235
Nice to meet you.

56
00:05:02,475 --> 00:05:04,590
Excuse me. Oolong tea.

57
00:05:04,590 --> 00:05:06,410
Thank you.

58
00:05:07,805 --> 00:05:09,510
Thanks.

59
00:05:09,510 --> 00:05:13,650
Kakeru, were you
in Cultural Anthropology this morning?

60
00:05:14,285 --> 00:05:15,430
Huh? Yeah.

61
00:05:15,430 --> 00:05:18,860
I knew it! I saw you leaving the classroom.

62
00:05:18,860 --> 00:05:21,190
What a relief!

63
00:05:21,190 --> 00:05:22,090
Why?

64
00:05:22,090 --> 00:05:25,000
Well, I help Koharu with her classes.

65
00:05:25,000 --> 00:05:28,110
The volunteer club helps out, too.

66
00:05:28,110 --> 00:05:28,920
Oh?

67
00:05:28,920 --> 00:05:32,630
But no one can make
the Monday morning class.

68
00:05:32,630 --> 00:05:35,290
I've been really worried.

69
00:05:35,290 --> 00:05:40,210
So, Kakeru, could you sit
with Koharu during class?

70
00:05:40,210 --> 00:05:40,840
What?

71
00:05:40,840 --> 00:05:44,170
Meet her at the student plaza
before class and guide her...

72
00:05:44,170 --> 00:05:45,260
Wait.

73
00:05:45,260 --> 00:05:46,540
Yuuko, you can't just...

74
00:05:46,540 --> 00:05:48,165
But I'm worried!

75
00:05:48,165 --> 00:05:50,385
Hey, you should just do it.

76
00:05:51,315 --> 00:05:52,800
Please!

77
00:05:52,800 --> 00:05:54,215
Okay?

78
00:05:54,215 --> 00:05:55,415
Please!

79
00:06:10,240 --> 00:06:12,010
Is that you, Kakeru?

80
00:06:12,820 --> 00:06:13,820
Huh?

81
00:06:15,850 --> 00:06:18,120
Thanks for coming today.

82
00:06:20,220 --> 00:06:21,550
Right.

83
00:06:36,580 --> 00:06:37,810
I'll get it.

84
00:06:39,120 --> 00:06:41,180
Sorry about that.

85
00:06:42,376 --> 00:06:46,666
Lost items are the worst
for the visually impaired.

86
00:06:47,830 --> 00:06:49,160
I see.

87
00:06:49,939 --> 00:06:53,039
I dropped a very important bookmark
the other day.

88
00:06:56,860 --> 00:06:58,120
Oh.

89
00:07:03,180 --> 00:07:05,090
Shall we go?

90
00:07:20,232 --> 00:07:22,298
[Temporary Class Cancellation Notice]
[Course: Cultural Anthropology]

91
00:07:22,298 --> 00:07:24,240
Class is canceled...

92
00:07:24,240 --> 00:07:25,530
Huh?

93
00:07:25,530 --> 00:07:28,305
Sorry, I should have checked.

94
00:07:28,305 --> 00:07:30,945
No, I should have too.

95
00:07:32,730 --> 00:07:36,100
Oh... Well, then...

96
00:07:37,030 --> 00:07:38,260
Um...

97
00:07:41,225 --> 00:07:45,810
If you'd like, let's kill time together
until the next class?

98
00:07:51,100 --> 00:07:53,610
How did you know it was me earlier?

99
00:07:53,610 --> 00:07:54,610
Huh?

100
00:07:55,405 --> 00:07:58,960
You called out to me
before I said anything.

101
00:07:58,960 --> 00:08:01,870
Oh, it was your footsteps.

102
00:08:03,245 --> 00:08:05,130
Footsteps?

103
00:08:05,130 --> 00:08:08,900
They sounded like
the ones I heard at the party.

104
00:08:11,070 --> 00:08:12,490
Oh.

105
00:08:15,455 --> 00:08:16,770
Huh?

106
00:08:16,770 --> 00:08:19,455
Oh, sorry.

107
00:08:19,455 --> 00:08:22,025
You just seem unique, Kakeru.

108
00:08:25,060 --> 00:08:28,540
People are usually overly careful with me.

109
00:08:29,360 --> 00:08:33,967
Like earlier,
people moved out of my way, right?

110
00:08:34,720 --> 00:08:36,280
You noticed?

111
00:08:36,928 --> 00:08:39,853
It always makes me feel bad.

112
00:08:39,853 --> 00:08:44,615
So when someone like you just says
"Oh," and moves on,

113
00:08:44,615 --> 00:08:46,195
it puts me at ease.

114
00:08:50,970 --> 00:08:52,090
Oh.

115
00:08:56,110 --> 00:08:58,960
What's that? What are you reading?

116
00:09:00,085 --> 00:09:03,600
"The Margin and the Bloom"
by Shuntaro Asama.

117
00:09:03,600 --> 00:09:05,290
The Margin and the Bloom?

118
00:09:05,290 --> 00:09:07,165
You like it too, Kakeru?

119
00:09:07,165 --> 00:09:09,155
Oh, no, not really.

120
00:09:11,010 --> 00:09:13,770
It's just the first novel I ever read.

121
00:09:14,440 --> 00:09:16,310
Really?

122
00:09:18,920 --> 00:09:21,530
It's so thick in braille.

123
00:09:23,260 --> 00:09:25,830
Want to try reading it?

124
00:09:33,370 --> 00:09:38,440
One page of a normal book
becomes about twice as long in braille.

125
00:09:43,740 --> 00:09:48,910
"In that town, this flower
always bloomed when winter came."

126
00:09:49,715 --> 00:09:51,780
Can you read braille?

127
00:09:51,780 --> 00:09:55,535
No, I just remember the line.

128
00:09:55,535 --> 00:09:57,975
You must really love it.

129
00:10:00,240 --> 00:10:01,240
Oh.

130
00:10:04,600 --> 00:10:07,080
That's the first time I've heard you laugh.

131
00:10:08,780 --> 00:10:09,970
Yeah.

132
00:10:29,435 --> 00:10:30,840
I'm home.

133
00:10:30,840 --> 00:10:32,980
Welcome back.

134
00:10:32,980 --> 00:10:34,955
Dinner's almost ready.

135
00:10:34,955 --> 00:10:36,035
Okay.

136
00:10:40,520 --> 00:10:42,710
Did something good happen?

137
00:10:43,480 --> 00:10:44,980
Not really.

138
00:10:46,650 --> 00:10:48,690
Don't forget your medicine.

139
00:10:49,820 --> 00:10:51,020
Okay.

140
00:10:53,730 --> 00:10:57,940
[Dr. Miura]

141
00:11:03,135 --> 00:11:05,650
Reading together on the terrace?

142
00:11:05,650 --> 00:11:07,415
So youthful.

143
00:11:07,415 --> 00:11:10,085
We were just killing time.

144
00:11:10,870 --> 00:11:12,790
But you had fun, right?

145
00:11:16,775 --> 00:11:19,480
Koharu was cool, wasn't she?

146
00:11:19,480 --> 00:11:21,650
She's always so positive.

147
00:11:21,650 --> 00:11:23,570
Wait, why are you here, Yuuko?

148
00:11:23,570 --> 00:11:29,035
What's the big deal?
I used to come over all the time.

149
00:11:29,035 --> 00:11:31,875
What? Are you two...

150
00:11:33,000 --> 00:11:36,430
Why does your mind always go there?

151
00:11:37,850 --> 00:11:40,140
I'm so jealous...

152
00:11:41,745 --> 00:11:45,300
Sorry, gotta take this call.

153
00:11:45,300 --> 00:11:46,330
Okay.

154
00:12:03,435 --> 00:12:04,990
Hello?

155
00:12:04,990 --> 00:12:05,910
Hey.

156
00:12:05,910 --> 00:12:09,510
Has Kakeru always been like that?

157
00:12:09,510 --> 00:12:11,050
Like what?

158
00:12:11,050 --> 00:12:15,535
Well, he talks fine,
but he never lets you get closer.

159
00:12:15,535 --> 00:12:19,285
It's like he doesn't want to enjoy himself.

160
00:12:33,695 --> 00:12:37,130
This is Kakeru in high school.

161
00:12:37,130 --> 00:12:38,170
Huh?

162
00:12:39,660 --> 00:12:41,740
Whoa!

163
00:12:44,405 --> 00:12:46,830
That's a million-watt smile!

164
00:12:46,830 --> 00:12:49,390
It's you, and this is...

165
00:12:54,025 --> 00:12:57,340
Kakeru's best friend.

166
00:12:57,340 --> 00:12:58,765
Hmm.

167
00:12:58,765 --> 00:13:00,405
But he was in an accident.

168
00:13:02,655 --> 00:13:03,900
Huh?

169
00:13:03,900 --> 00:13:08,688
Actually, I might not be able to go.

170
00:13:08,688 --> 00:13:10,728
I have class.

171
00:13:13,880 --> 00:13:17,060
But it's his third-year memorial.

172
00:13:17,060 --> 00:13:21,600
Haruto's mom was asking if you'd come.

173
00:13:23,910 --> 00:13:25,030
Sorry.

174
00:13:28,750 --> 00:13:34,920
That's why Kakeru is scared of having fun.

175
00:14:02,551 --> 00:14:06,969
[I'm sorry, something urgent came up
and I can't make it today.]

176
00:14:06,969 --> 00:14:08,182
[Okay!]

177
00:14:18,910 --> 00:14:20,190
Kakeru.

178
00:14:21,860 --> 00:14:22,920
Hey.

179
00:14:33,210 --> 00:14:35,461
Did something happen?

180
00:14:35,461 --> 00:14:37,641
I heard from Koharu.

181
00:14:43,425 --> 00:14:47,030
Can I quit this support stuff?

182
00:14:47,030 --> 00:14:48,030
Huh?

183
00:14:49,180 --> 00:14:51,020
Someone else can do it, right?

184
00:14:51,890 --> 00:14:54,220
You just asked out of convenience.

185
00:14:57,140 --> 00:15:00,430
Sorry. Find someone else.

186
00:15:01,245 --> 00:15:03,350
Wait!

187
00:15:03,350 --> 00:15:05,290
It's not just for my convenience!

188
00:15:07,866 --> 00:15:12,980
Of course, I asked
because I was worried about Koharu.

189
00:15:12,980 --> 00:15:14,120
But...

190
00:15:15,740 --> 00:15:21,190
I also thought it might be good for you
to connect with someone, too.

191
00:15:25,870 --> 00:15:27,070
I'm sorry.

192
00:16:04,880 --> 00:16:06,610
Is someone there?

193
00:16:10,840 --> 00:16:12,760
Kakeru?

194
00:16:20,870 --> 00:16:22,430
What are you doing?

195
00:16:25,685 --> 00:16:29,350
Apparently, anyone's allowed
to play this piano.

196
00:16:29,350 --> 00:16:31,570
So I thought I'd try.

197
00:16:33,060 --> 00:16:36,470
Believe it or not,
but I used to want to be a pianist.

198
00:16:38,080 --> 00:16:39,490
Oh?

199
00:16:43,750 --> 00:16:46,830
Are you wondering
how I can play without seeing?

200
00:16:47,500 --> 00:16:48,770
Well...

201
00:16:58,430 --> 00:16:59,450
Yeah.

202
00:17:03,080 --> 00:17:05,420
Those memories are still there.

203
00:17:10,030 --> 00:17:11,950
Losing something...

204
00:17:12,992 --> 00:17:15,532
doesn't mean it all becomes zero.

205
00:17:17,380 --> 00:17:24,300
My body remembers
how much I enjoyed playing back then.

206
00:17:26,810 --> 00:17:28,580
Doesn't that...

207
00:17:37,560 --> 00:17:39,320
feel painful?

208
00:17:41,720 --> 00:17:44,080
Remembering when you could still see...

209
00:17:48,930 --> 00:17:51,210
It was, at first.

210
00:17:53,260 --> 00:17:57,380
I mean, I couldn't even get
toothpaste on my toothbrush.

211
00:17:59,220 --> 00:18:02,170
I thought I was pathetic.

212
00:18:04,080 --> 00:18:07,210
But then I realized something.

213
00:18:09,820 --> 00:18:12,000
You can't change the past,

214
00:18:13,230 --> 00:18:17,010
but how you accept what happened
is up to you.

215
00:18:20,940 --> 00:18:23,530
The hurdles became much higher.

216
00:18:24,336 --> 00:18:27,206
But that doesn't mean I can't clear them.

217
00:18:28,330 --> 00:18:32,920
In fact, it feels amazing
when you manage to jump over them.

218
00:18:35,330 --> 00:18:37,330
Whatever it takes...

219
00:18:38,210 --> 00:18:42,030
Sounds. Smells. Old memories.

220
00:18:43,030 --> 00:18:44,790
I'll use everything.

221
00:18:49,490 --> 00:18:51,220
Watch me, okay?

222
00:20:13,026 --> 00:20:14,406
Koharu!

223
00:20:19,620 --> 00:20:21,030
Kakeru?

224
00:20:24,920 --> 00:20:28,480
Sorry for missing class today.

225
00:20:31,450 --> 00:20:35,465
And about the bookmark, too.

226
00:20:35,465 --> 00:20:37,000
Huh?

227
00:20:37,000 --> 00:20:38,610
I actually saw it.

228
00:20:39,480 --> 00:20:41,660
When you dropped the bookmark.

229
00:20:45,040 --> 00:20:49,430
But... I didn't pick it up.

230
00:20:51,800 --> 00:20:53,870
I didn't want to get involved.

231
00:20:56,930 --> 00:20:58,650
I see.

232
00:21:00,690 --> 00:21:03,950
But you said it yourself earlier.

233
00:21:05,120 --> 00:21:10,070
That losing something
doesn't mean it all becomes zero.

234
00:21:36,960 --> 00:21:38,170
The bookmark...

235
00:21:39,430 --> 00:21:41,110
It was still there.

236
00:21:49,202 --> 00:21:50,870
Starting next week...

237
00:21:52,700 --> 00:21:55,240
I'll go to class again.

238
00:21:58,850 --> 00:21:59,880
Okay.

239
00:22:05,930 --> 00:22:08,183
By the way...

240
00:22:08,183 --> 00:22:09,183
Yes?

241
00:22:10,600 --> 00:22:14,010
What was on that bookmark?

242
00:22:14,680 --> 00:22:17,240
It was in braille, right?

243
00:22:18,128 --> 00:22:21,950
It's a list of things
I want to do in my life.

244
00:22:21,950 --> 00:22:23,360
Oh.

245
00:22:34,290 --> 00:22:35,860
The first one is...

246
00:22:38,030 --> 00:22:40,260
To play the piano again.

247
00:22:43,210 --> 00:22:44,590
And the second?

248
00:22:46,645 --> 00:22:50,330
This one is quite a high hurdle.

249
00:22:50,330 --> 00:22:52,010
So it's worth it, right?

250
00:22:54,480 --> 00:22:56,010
The second is...

251
00:22:59,870 --> 00:23:01,470
Why?

252
00:23:06,075 --> 00:23:08,360
Why is it always her?

253
00:23:08,360 --> 00:23:10,260
Isn't it unfair?

254
00:23:11,145 --> 00:23:13,986
It's still just a possibility.

255
00:23:13,986 --> 00:23:15,686
It took so long...

256
00:23:19,687 --> 00:23:23,437
It took so long
to finally start looking forward.

257
00:23:25,530 --> 00:23:27,160
The second is...

258
00:23:29,400 --> 00:23:33,060
setting off fireworks.

259
00:23:34,940 --> 00:23:36,550
Fireworks?

260
00:23:37,630 --> 00:23:39,440
<i>That was...</i>

261
00:23:40,170 --> 00:23:41,700
<i>the beginning of us.</i>

262
00:23:45,155 --> 00:23:46,970
Asakusa on Sunday?

263
00:23:46,970 --> 00:23:48,175
Watch out.

264
00:23:48,175 --> 00:23:49,885
Get caught? Your arm.

265
00:23:49,885 --> 00:23:53,630
Interacting with people
means getting to know them, right?

266
00:23:53,630 --> 00:23:56,345
For example, what would you like to know?

267
00:23:56,345 --> 00:23:59,515
Why did you lose your sight?
